

Q1) Explain about the Marker interface?

Ans)  Marker Interface :  The empty interface is Known as Marker interface or tag interface.Some of the predefined marker interface  in java are :
     ====================  1) java.io.Serializable.
     					   2) java.lang.Clonable .
     These kind of marker interface used to specify certain type of special behavior of our object.
     
     Example :
    ===========
    
    public interface Student{
    
    }
    
    If we wants to group multiple objects to a special type then also we can make use marker interface .				   
